quran[40]{c,v,t}:
  77,1,"By the [winds] sent forth for a purpose"
  77,2,and gales that rage on and on
  77,3,scattering things around
  77,4,then dividing them all up
  77,5,and delivering a Reminder
  77,6,either as a plea or a warning
  77,7,you (all) are surely promised something inevitable
  77,8,When the stars fade away
  77,9,when the sky splits open
  77,10,when mountains are pulverized
  77,11,and when messengers´ time is set
  77,12,till which day will they be put off? The Day for Sorting Things Out
  77,13,"Till the day for Sorting [things] out"
  77,14,What will make you realize what the day for Sorting is
  77,15,It will be too bad for rejectors on that day
  77,16,Did We not wipe out ancient men
  77,17,Then We followed them up with later ones
  77,18,Thus We deal with criminals
  77,19,It will be too bad for rejectors on that day
  77,20,Do We not create you (all) from a despised fluid
  77,21,We place it in a firm resting-place
  77,22,for a known period
  77,23,We measure it out and how favored are Those Who measure it
  77,24,It will be too bad for rejectors on that day
  77,25,Have We not placed the earth as a round up
  77,26,for the living and the dead
  77,27,We have planted lofty headlands on it and offered you (all) fresh water to drink
  77,28,It will be too bad for rejectors on that day
  77,29,Hurry off to whatever you have been rejecting
  77,30,Hurry away to shade which has three sections
  77,31,which is not shady nor any help against flame
  77,32,"It throws off sparks like a palace [on fire]"
  77,33,"[bright] as a yellow camel herd"
  77,34,It will be too bad for rejectors on that day
  77,35,"This will be a day when they will not utter [a sound]"
  77,36,nor will they be permitted to offer any excuse
  77,37,It will be too bad for rejectors on that day
  77,38,"This is a day for Sorting [things] out; We shall bring you (all) together with the original men"
  77,39,"If you have any scheme, then scheme against me"
  77,40,It will be too bad for rejectors on that day! Those who Do their Duty